*** ChanServ Help - Command: SET TOPICLOCK ***
Enables or disables the Topic Lock option for a channel.
When it is set, ChanServ will not allow the channel topic
to be changed unless access permits. Also, ChanServ will only
give access to the TOPIC command to the level you specify.
level can be VOP, HOP, AOP, SOP, CFOUNDER or FOUNDER.
When OFF is specified this option is disabled.
 
Syntax:
/cs SET #channel TOPICLOCK level
 
Examples:
/cs SET #IRCHelp TOPICLOCK AOP
/cs SET #Italia TOPICLOCK FOUNDER
/cs SET #SoleLuna TOPICLOCK OFF
 
Type /join #IRCHelp for more information.
*** End of Help ***
